
|WKBSyntax: |YKBget <object> [from <object>]
        |YKBget all <object> [from <object>]
 
|WKBDESCRIPTION
|WKO===========
 
|YKOGet an item.  You can also |YKB"get all"|YKO.  If the thing you want is in something
else, type |YKB"get <object> from <object>" |YKOsuch as "get knife from bag".
Similarly if you're getting something from a corpse.  You would type
something like "get coins from corpse" or "get knife from corpse".

The second method allows you to get all of one specific object instead
of everything.  You do do things such as|CKB:

   get all sword OR get all sword from bag.
 
|WKBSee also: |YKBdrop, put, give
